      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Auxiliary Circle&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>A circle drawn with the center C and T.A. as a diameter is called the Auxiliary Circle of the hyperbola. Equation of the auxiliary circle is ${{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}={{a}^{2}}$.</p><p>Note from the figure that $\\text{P}$ and $\\text{Q}$ are called the \"Corresponding Points\" on the hyperbola and the auxiliary circle. ' $\\theta $ is called the eccentric angle of the point ' $\\text{P}$ ' on the hyperbola $(0\\le \\theta &lt;2\\pi )$.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"400\" height=\"156\"></p>",
